n, teacher.Please stop dancing. ”\nBut the servant thought without listening to him.&page&\'In the meantime, I have been weaving people\'s high blood (I have paid for expensive interest).\nThe servant started playing harder again.&page&As a result, the Jews jumped higher than before, and the coat was now torn and caught in a thorn bush.\n\"Oh, I\'m dead!\" Jews shouted.\"I\'ll give you everything to ask anything, please stop playing the violin, and I will give my wallet with my gold coins.\"&page&“If you are so generous,” the servant said.“I stop playing too.But you have to be responsible for words.If you don\'t do it, please dance more badly. ”\nThus, the servant who took his wallet was slowly on my way.&page&The Jews, who were standing dazzling and watching the servants for a long time, said, when the servant disappeared completely far away, he screamed at the whale whale.&page&“Did you see the musicians of the ruined guy?I will hold your own guy.You\'ll be chased after the shoe sole worn out!A child like this raw alchi!I\'ll put a bunch of coins in your mouth and make it with muk bowl! ”&page&The Jews sweared and sweared and hesitated until they touched their strength.\nThen he was a bit energy, and he took his breath and ran to the city and went to the judge.&page&\"Judge,\" the Jew said.“I have something to sue.On the road that I was released today, I was robbed and struggling with a person like a rugged party!If you saw it, even cold stones felt compassion for me.My clothes have been torn, and there\'s no place in my body that is not stabbed and scratched.In addition, the one has lost his wallet with gold coins.Please put him in jail right away! ”&page&\"Is it a soldier?\"“Is the soldier stabbed you with a cavalry?”&page&\"No no, it\'s not!\"“He didn\'t have a sword.I was carrying a gun in one bag, not a sword.I have a violin on my neck.So it\'s easy to find him. ”\nSo the judge sent people to find him.&page&People found a good servant.As he was slowly on his 